status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4ui5","text":"Anesthetize rat with isofluorane (5% induction phase, 2% maintenance phase)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"20otu","text":"Place rat head gently with ears bar onto the stereotaxic equipment","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8adu0","text":"Scalpel + Scalpel holder = incision middle of rat head","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"74c9v","text":"Place 4 hemostats in each extremity of the incision (opening in square shape)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"810ir","text":"Remove tissue of the skull with the not-cutting side of scalpel (scratch in order to see bregma and lambda as better as possible, can bleed for a prolonged time, apply saline as necessary)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ehj62","text":"Check skull horizontality: place drill (adjust with the yellow tool) + take DV in lambda and bregma by placing the drill on the cranium (neither above nor pressing it). If not leveled (+/- 0.1 between Bregma and Lambda), adjust as necessary ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7ut8v","text":"Drill very slowly. Regularly check the depth of craniotomy.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2ucm7","text":"Inject vector solutions using a 10 µL Hamilton syringe fitted with a glass capillary","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"jjr4","text":"Perform infusion at 0.4 µL/min and let the needle in place for 4 minutes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"65icp","text":"Seal craniotomoy with bonewax using a small spatula","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
